channel.title: Interleaved RSS Feed
channel.description: This is an interleaved feed of the most recent entries from each RSS source, skipping any feeds with errors.

item.title: Devastation in Gaza as Israel wages war on Hamas
item.description: Five Israeli soldiers have been killed in northern Gaza where Israel is once again operating despite having previously said it cleared the area of Hamas. Follow live updates.

item.title: Slovakia prime minster's condition stabilized after shooting, deputy says
item.description: Slovakian Prime Minister Robert Fico's condition has been stabilized overnight, although his condition is still serious, his deputy said early Thursday.

item.title: Russia advances in Ukraine as Putin meets Xi in China
item.description: Russian President Vladimir Putin has met Chinese leader Xi Jinping in Beijing, emboldened by the survival of his wartime economy and Russia's advances in Ukraine. Follow for live updates

item.title: 'The world's fault': Zelenskyy speaks out amid Russian assault
item.description: ABC News had an exclusive interview with the Ukrainian President Volodymyr Zelenskyy on Thursday.

item.title: Slovakia's prime minister expected to survive after shooting
item.description: Slovakian Prime Minister Robert Fico is expected to survive after being shot five times in what officials described as a politically motivated assassination attempt.

item.title: Michael Cohen to return to witness stand for 3rd day of testimony in Trump trial
item.description: Former Trump attorney Michael Cohen is set to return to the witness stand Thursday to face a full day of cross-examination in Donald Trump's criminal hush money trial.

item.title: May 15, 2024 - Russia's war in Ukraine
item.description: US Secretary of State Antony Blinken announced $2 billion in military financing for Ukraine as Russia is pushing into northeastern part of the country.

item.title: US soldier detained in Russia 'admitted guilt,' state media reports
item.description: Gordon Black, the U.S. soldier detained in Russia, has "admitted guilt" on a charge of theft, according to TASS, a state-owned news service.

item.title: May 14, 2024 - Russia's war in Ukraine
item.description: Antony Blinken met with Volodymyr Zelensky in Kyiv earlier Tuesday, where the Ukrainian president told the US secretary of state that Ukraine urgently needs more air defenses.

item.title: Hawaii native Savannah Gankiewicz crowned Miss USA after the previous winner resigned
item.description: Savannah Gankiewicz of Hawaii has been crowned Miss USA 2023, more than a week after the previous titleholder resigned citing her mental health
